<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=10093831854675></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10093831854675><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=10093831854675>RE: Need some advice.</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=10093831854675#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=130965><span id= >Xorannder</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Dec 26th 11:13 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I would definately say that Erudites are one of the more difficult races to begin with.  As mentioned, they have low dex/agility as well as low strength and in addition, cannot see very well in the dark.  Eventhough the night vision has been somewhat improved, I still keep my Chill Sight up all the time.  Mana is life for a Wizard and it is that simple.  The more base intelligence you have, the more slots you will have open in the 50+ levels that give you additional MANA, not int.  Its all in how you care to play your character. If you are satisfied with max 200int and an extra 50 mana as well as the advantage of an easier newbie zone and nightvision then there is absolutely nothing wrong with that.  It is my view, however, that the more Total mana a Wizard has, the more useful they will be in the 50+ levels.  At lower levels (25 and below), the Erudite may be at a slight disadvantage.  Which race you choose is personal preference.  Good Day.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
