<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100824234444586></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100824234444586><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=100824234444586>One more thing</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=100824234444586#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=119184><span id= >Raythe</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>7 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Dec 13th 6:19 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I know what every wizard wants: a way to draw more aggro.  Right?  Well at level 35 I was trying to help my level 24 warrior pal get some fast exp.  Now wizards are not known for their PL'ing skills, but I told him I'd give it a shot.  Over the course of our crazy romp across South Karana trying to find something good for us to kill, I discovered that casting Steelskin on myself drew a whole lot of aggro every time.  First I'd make sure Greater Shielding and Steelskin were up.  Then I'd nuke a gnoll (which conned red to my buddy) with Shock of Ice (or is it Ice Shock?  the level 34 one) and he'd come running over to whoop on me for a bit.  As soon as the gnoll got to me, my warrior buddy started whacking away.  If my steelskin dropped or the gnoll switched aggro to the warrior, I'd just throw up another Steelskin and aggro would come right back to me.  (If interruptions became a problem I'd stun first, back up and then steelskin myself.)  Once my buddy got him to the run phase I'd throw on Bonds of Force if I hadn't done so already and in the end my friend got all the exp for killing a red con mob.  Now I know this doesn't compare to a druid's ability to PL by any stretch of the imagination, but since all we had in the way of heals was bind wounds this was the best we could do.  One caveat though: the mob had to con light blue or higher to me for this to work.  Green mobs wouldn't bother aggroing me at all once my friend started attacking.  I was doing 310 with my nuke and could cast stun twice for 45 damage and friend would still get exp when we were attacking the Tesch Mas Gnolls that spawn at the spires outside of Paw.  The only drawback to this technique is that I ran through about 40 Jaspers in a couple hours.  But oh well it's easier to get money than it is to find a tank who plays as well as my buddy does.  That's all I got for tonight (ack early morning). Later all.<br>Oli  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
