<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=10079321313568></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10079321313568><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=10079321313568>Erudite Wizard Advice</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=10079321313568#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=98912><span id= >Skycaster</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Dec 9th 4:08 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>At low levels Wizards can be a real Challange to play. As an Erudite you start off in Tox Forest. Your vision is not very good and Tox forest is Dark to start with. Start off hunting close to the guards because you will have to run to them often at first. Remember the Guards will not attack a Heretic Prophet so run for the zone if one shows up. After you make lvl 4 Pack your Bags and take the Boat to Qeynos and get a bind there.<br>Hunt around in North Qeynos and Qeynos Hills with a small group that includes a tank type. use this time to also learn to control how you cast. You must learn to cast in a balanced manner. A big part of that is determined by how fast the other members of the group are doing damage. Learn to keep an eye on the Mobs heath and cast accordingly. Dont fall into the trap that many wizards do and think that you have to cast all out on something you are fighting. The tanks are there to take damage , let them do their job and take the hits. If you burn up all your mana and they are full health they will get tired of waiting for you to med all the time while they are good to go.You May want to avoid black Burrow until you lvl up a bit , Black Burrow is a Nightmare of trains for a wizard that is too low a lvl and you will get pounded into dust. After you make lvl 9 go back to Toxullia forest and pay a visit to Elial Brook. Bring a friend with you and kill him over and over. Spawn time is about 7 min. or so. Ignore his pet until Elial is dead. Elial will cast fear on you from time to time so dont have Sow on when fighting him or you may run far into the forest and right into the water. Save his bones and turn them in at the top of the mage guild in Erudin Palace. Name is Marvus or something like that.While you wait for him to spawn you may as well fish on the river bank. The Green Gill Salmon you catch there will bring about 4sp each. After you have dinged a couple times you may want to take a full group into the warrens. Great loot and descent exp for your lvl can be found there. But you may want to kill a truck load or two of Kobolds to help your faction with the Heretics to help to grease your way into the warrens ,after killing Elial Brook they will not be to pleased with you. After you make lvl 12 take yourself and your little group to the Island in erud's crossing, you remember you stop there on the trip from Qeynos to Erudin . Kill willowwisp's and pull zombies from the sunken ship with your group. There are times when your tank or somebody in your group may get into trouble and you may need to &quot;Overburn&quot; and aggro the mob onto you and take some damage. At later lvl's the mob should be snared by you or a group member and with Sow you can kite them around and cast a bit to help prevent an untimly death. Especially if your healer call's out OOM!.Magic caster type mobs dont seem to mind being snared and will Blast you anyway if snared so keep this in mind. After you leave &quot;Wisp Island&quot; in Erud's Crossing you may want to go to West Karana and get into a Bandit group( Hey! that was my Sash!)Beware of brigands. A little later on take a group into the Scarecrow Field and hunt &quot;Crow's&quot;. Poor loot descent EXP, Bring somebody that can track or has a Sense Undead spell and it will go better.Do Not attack Furball Miller , Tiny will not be happy and he will kill you fast at this lvl.Give those Sacks of Hay to Cleet Millers Old Lady and she will give you a touch of EXP. You may want to take your group to the Aviak City in South Karana or pull thing's to the bridge in East Karana or a trip to High Pass to hunt Gnolls , Be carful running thru North Karana , See all those Corpses laying around , those are Griffon Turd's so whatch where you step.<br>South Karana is a reasonably safe zone , not alot of things will aggro on you here unless you attack it, The John Tesh Gnolls ( hee hee ) will aggro on you and can be a handful depending on your groups lvl.After youv'e leveled up a bit more maybe a trip to hunt the splitpaw spires or the Orc side of High Pass ( Man I wish I could Get a Breeze or Clarity ) or Lake Rath. By now you have experienced many Resist's and learned that some spell's are all or nothing and some will hit for partial Resist's. It's a fact of life and as much as we hate it it will happen. But I know from grouping with others that Wizards are resisted less than other caster's. After the lvl your at by now you will have many good idea's on where to hunt and what to do. And this is just to give you some Idea's on things to hunt , there are so many other places to hunt and thing's to do I could not possibly list them here. Besides there is alot I don't know , But I do know this: Move the attack button on your keyboard from A to another spot ( Plus key maybe ? ), Don't cast an AOE type spell near Guards or any other high lvl NPC . Don't Cast an AOE spell in a crowded Dungeon. Don't stand too close to anything you cast an AOE spell on. AOE stands for Aggro On Erudite. Report your mana status to your group.Go Anon after you get port spells or be prepared for &quot;Tell Hell&quot; anytime you are in a city. Sell your weapons after lvl 30 , they are kinda useless after that , Melee a Hill Giant and you WILL go down. Going back and Killing Grimfeather for Revenge Does feel good.(/EM Kicks Grimfeathers corpse). Never Shake hands with a Troll ( Back Off Stinkfinger ! ). A Female Half Elf ranger on a corpse run warms the soul ( Sorry Baby I tried to Evak but I was getting hit). Playing a Wizard is playing with your Head , all Brains no Brawn. You are a Wizard not a Wizzy or a finger Wiggler or a Taxi, Be Proud Be Fair and Nuke em into dust !<br><br>Skycaster Graustark<br>LVL 40<br>Erudite Wizard of the Crimson Hands<br>Advocates of Light<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
