	   <tr><td colspan=2>Excellent!!  I had been thinking a couple of things since making that post.  One, is that Wizards needed the ability to memorize more spells.  I think you've covered that beautifully.  The other, is the ability for the Wizard and his familiar to location swap.  Activating this ability would require 100% of the Wizards mana, regardless of that value, and would have a regen time of 72 mins.  In this way, the Wizard could use the scouting ability of the familiar to take it somewhere difficult for the Wizard to reach.  But the familiar would have to be left in a safe location as the Wizard will need to med to full before making the exchange, leaving the familiar alone and unprotected.  I feel this makes for a usefull yet properly limited ability.  Again, I'd like to say great thinking to Tyronius and I look forward to reading his and others ideas and comments on this familiar concept.  =)<br>&nbsp;<br>-Maintaining the Honor of Test</td></tr>
